[A total of 2478 newly confirmed cases have been reported by China in the past 24 hours, compared with 3062 during the similar time frame [8-9 Feb 2020]. This brings the total number of reported confirmed cases to 42 638. In addition, 108 deaths were reported in this time period, bringing the total number of reported deaths to 1016. In the past 24 hours there have been 10 newly confirmed cases reported from Hong Kong and 1 newly confirmed case reported from Taiwan.

Similar to the period Friday [7 Feb 2020] to Saturday [8 Feb 2020], there was a decrease in the daily reported cases of 19.1%. One hopes this is a harbinger of decreasing transmission, although as previously mentioned, a good epidemic curve by date of onset of illness would be interesting to see, as date of confirmation testing is later than date of onset of illness, not necessarily due to laboratory delays, but related to early mild symptoms not leading to healthcare-seeking behaviors.

A good map of China showing provinces can be found at https://www.chinadiscovery.com/china-maps/china-provincial-map.html and a HealthMap/ProMED-mail map at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=6976117,155. - Mod.MPP]

