B. Singapore
Date: Mon 10 Feb 2020
Source: New Straits Times [edited]
https://www.nst.com.my/world/world/2020/02/564427/2-new-coronavirus-cases-emerge-singapore-tally-rises-45


Singapore's Ministry of Health (MOH) confirmed 2 more cases of the novel coronavirus (2019-nCoV) in the republic on Monday [10 Feb 2020] night, bringing the tally to 45.

The 2 cases comprise a 2-year-old Singaporean girl who was evacuated from Wuhan, China, on 30 Jan [2020] and a 37-year-old Singaporean man who works at the Certis Cisco Centre and had been on duty at the Chingay 2020 event.

The MOH added that of the 38 coronavirus patients still in hospital, 7 are in critical condition, while the rest are stable or improving, Bernama reported.

According to the MOH, epidemiological investigations and contact tracing have uncovered 3 infection clusters on the island: the Life Church and Missions Singapore; Chinese health products shop Yong Thai Hang; and the Grand Hyatt Singapore hotel, where a business meeting was held from [20-22 Jan 2020].

