[7] WHO situation report 21 (as of 10 Feb 2020*)
Date: Mon 10 Feb 2020
Source: World Health Organization [edited]
https://www.who.int/docs/default-source/coronaviruse/situation-reports/20200210-sitrep-21-ncov.pdf?sfvrsn=947679ef_2


*The situation report includes information provided by national authorities as of 10 a.m. Central European Time

Highlights
----------
- No new countries reported cases of 2019-nCoV in the past 24 hours.
- The WHO R&D Blueprint is a global strategy and preparedness plan that allows the rapid activation of R&D activities during epidemics. On [11-12 Feb 2020], WHO is convening a global research and innovation forum to mobilize international action and enable identification of key knowledge gaps and research priorities to contribute to the control of 2019-nCoV. The forum will include members of the scientific community, researchers from member states' public health agencies, regulatory experts, bioethicists with expertise in research in emergencies, and major funders of research related to 2019- nCoV.

[The figures provided in the report are the figures from the National Health Commission of China from 7 Feb 2020. The 10 Feb 2020 figures are included in Section [1] above. They are posted at approximately 7 p.m. (GMT-5), which is 1 a.m. (GMT+1) in Geneva. - Mod.MPP]

